Parliament, Thursday 5 April 2018 – The Chairperson of the Speakers' Forum of South Africa Ms Baleka Mbete and the European Union Commissioner for International Cooperation and Development Neven Mimica will collectively lead high powered delegations expected at the launch of a R140 million partnership programme aimed at strengthening the legislative sector at the Sheraton Hotel today. The partnership programme is aimed at enhancing legislative oversight while also strengthening citizen participation in legislative processes. The deliverables of the five-year programme, cutting across the fifth and the sixth terms of the South African legislatures, will be outlined at the launch event. Speaker Baleka Mbete and Commissioner Mimica will address the ceremony which begins after the end of day-1 of the Speakers Forum meeting that is attended by Presiding Officers of the country's ten legislatures today and civil society representatives The partnership programme seeks to also realise better legislative oversight through inter alia, building a capable and developmental legislative structures. DETAILS OF THE LAUNCH CEREMONY ARE AS FOLLOWS: DATE: Thursday, 5 April 2018
	TIME: 18.00 for 18.30
	VENUE: Sheraton Hotel, 643 Stanza Bopape Street, Pretoria Members of the Media who wish to cover the launch of the SALS-EU Programme should RSVP Mlindi Mpindi on 081 716 7329 or: mmpindi@parliament.gov.za and also please copy: mdlula@parliament.gov.za ISSUED BY PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA ON BEHALF OF THE SPEAKERS’ FORUM OF THE LEGISLATIVE SECTOR OF SOUTH AFRICA Enquiries: Moloto Mothapo – 082 370 6930 Although ordinary citizens may not submit bills to Parliament, they may lobby MPs or committees to introduce legislation that deals with their concerns.Read more